You are implementing the Stage 4 TTS Rendering panel (`components/stages/Stage4TtsRendering.tsx`) for a video production pipeline editor. This client component displays TTS audio segments with per-row waveform playback, batch render controls, and per-segment re-render.

Requirements
1. Props: `onAdvance: () => void`.
2. Toolbar: [Render All] and [Render Missing] buttons. Both trigger `POST /api/pipeline/tts-render/run` (with and without `segments` filter). Show batch progress bar.
3. Segment table columns: #, segment ID, status badge (done/missing/error), [▶] play button, [↺] re-render.
4. Row expansion on click: shows WaveSurfer.js waveform for the segment WAV file and raw TTS text. Waveform initialized on expand only.
5. Batch progress bar: shows current segment ID being rendered and overall percent.
6. Per-row [↺] re-render: triggers `POST /api/pipeline/tts-render/run` with `{ segments: [segmentId] }`. Shows inline `SseLogPanel`.
7. Load segments: `GET /api/pipeline/tts-render/segments` on mount and after each render.
8. `'use client'` directive.

