Prompt Dependencies:
- types_TypeScript.prompt — provides shared types
- sse_log_panel_TypeScriptReact.prompt — provides `SseLogPanel`

Instructions
- WaveSurfer initialization on row expand: `const ws = WaveSurfer.create({ container: waveformRef.current, url: `/api/audio/${segmentId}.wav`, height: 64, waveColor: '#4ade80', progressColor: '#166534' })`.
- Store WaveSurfer instances in a `useRef<Map<string, WaveSurfer>>` to avoid re-initialization.
- [▶] play: `wavesurfer.playPause()`.
- Audio URL: serve WAV files from `outputs/tts/{segmentId}.wav` — needs an audio serving route (similar to video route) or use a static file server.
- SSE events from render: `{ type: 'segment', segmentId, status }` updates row status in real time.
- Batch progress: track `currentSegment` and `completedCount` from SSE events.
- [Advance →] button enabled when all segments have `status: 'done'`.

Deliverable
- `components/stages/Stage4TtsRendering.tsx` — TTS segment rendering panel with WaveSurfer waveforms.

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- `wavesurfer.js` npm package is installed.
- WAV files are served via a separate audio API route (analogous to the video route).

Please produce production-ready prompt content that will generate the module consistent with the above.
